            <thetext>To allow server side rendered mobile pages / to create mobile apps without (or less JS knowledge), we should allow to create mobile UIs from HTML.

e.g.:

&lt;div data-class=&quot;qx.mobile.page.Navigation&quot; data-title=&quot;My first Page&quot; data-showBack=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
   &lt;div data-class=&quot;qx.mobile.ui.Button&quot; data-value=&quot;Hello World&quot; data-icon=&quot;world.png /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


The HTML is evaluated when the application is started and the corresponding widget hierarchy is created. Whenever HTML-Templates are loaded the same process should be applied. For that we should create factory methods that take the element and create the right widget for it.</thetext>
